  <section id="accuracy">
    <h2>1. Accuracy and No Warranty</h2>
    <p>EDU Mileage+ produces trip records, GPS routes, mileage calculations, and
    reimbursement reports on a best-effort basis using your device&rsquo;s
    location services, motion sensors, and geofencing. While we make every
    reasonable effort to deliver accurate results, accuracy is not guaranteed.
    Trips may be missed, mileage may be over- or under-reported, and sync events
    may be delayed by factors outside our control, including iOS background
    execution policies, GPS signal availability, and network conditions.</p>

    <p>You are solely responsible for reviewing the records produced by the App
    before submitting them to any employer, tax authority, or other party. The
    App is intended to assist with recordkeeping, not to replace your own
    judgment about what is accurate or complete.</p>

    <p>The App is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; without warranty of any kind. To
    the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, whether
    express, implied, or statutory, including warranties of merchantability,
    fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.</p>

    <p>Reimbursement disputes between you and your employer are solely between
    you and your employer. We are not a party to any reimbursement decision and
    do not guarantee any specific reimbursement outcome.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="tax">
    <h2>2. Tax Information Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>The IRS Annual Report feature in EDU Mileage+ produces a summary of your
    trip records intended for informational purposes only. It is not tax advice
    and is not a substitute for professional tax preparation.</p>

    <p>You should consult a qualified tax professional regarding the
    deductibility of unreimbursed business expenses, the applicable mileage
    rates for your situation, and proper reporting on your tax return. Tax
    treatment of mileage varies by jurisdiction, employment status, and personal
    circumstances.</p>

    <p>The mileage rates displayed in the App reflect IRS standard mileage rates
    published at the time each trip was recorded. You are responsible for
    confirming the correct rate for your specific situation, including any
    mid-year rate changes that may have been issued after a trip was logged.</p>

    <p>Under IRS regulations, taxpayers are generally required to retain
    supporting documentation for business expense deductions for at least three
    years after the return is filed. The records produced by the App do not
    relieve you of any retention obligations imposed by tax law.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="recordkeeping">
    <h2>3. Recordkeeping Responsibility</h2>
    <p>EDU Mileage+ is a productivity tool. It is not a system of record for
    your employer&rsquo;s reimbursement program, nor is it a substitute for any
    recordkeeping requirements imposed by your employer&rsquo;s policies,
    district regulations, or applicable law.</p>

    <p>Many districts require additional documentation beyond what the App
    captures &mdash; for example, approved travel authorization forms, signed
    receipts, specific reporting templates, or supervisor approvals. You are
    responsible for understanding and complying with the recordkeeping
    requirements of your employer.</p>

    <p>If your employer requires specific information not captured by the App,
    you should maintain that information separately. The records produced by the
    App are intended to supplement your own recordkeeping practices, not replace
    them.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="trademarks">
    <h2>4. Trademarks</h2>
    <p>Apple, the Apple logo, iPhone, iPad, App Store, iCloud, and CloudKit are
    trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries.
    EDU Mileage+ is an independent product not affiliated with Apple Inc.</p>

    <p>EDU Plus Apps and EDU Mileage+ are trademarks of the developer. Other
    product and company names mentioned within the App or on this site may be
    trademarks of their respective owners.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <h2>5. Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about these notices can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:support@eduplusapps.com">support@eduplusapps.com</a>.</p>
  </section>

</main>

